{"id":49182,"date":"2025-12-23T21:52:34","date_gmt":"2025-12-23T18:52:34","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/e-museum.kz\/exhibit\/68da7f5c9f2f2ba6d-en\/"},"modified":"2025-12-31T13:04:36","modified_gmt":"2025-12-31T10:04:36","slug":"68da7f5c9f2f2ba6d-en","status":"publish","type":"exhibit","link":"https:\/\/e-museum.kz\/en\/exhibit\/68da7f5c9f2f2ba6d-en\/","title":{"rendered":"Congratulatory Letter."},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Congratulatory Letter<br \/>\nThis is a beautifully decorated congratulatory message presented on a stylized sheet. The edges of the sheet are adorned with traditional patterns and designed to resemble ancient parchment.<\/p>\n<p>At the top, in red letters, is the greeting: &#171;A\u0441\u0430 \u049b\u04b1\u0440\u043c\u0435\u0442\u0442\u0456 \u0428\u043e\u0442\u0430!&#187; \u2014 &#171;Dearly Respected Shota!&#187;<\/p>\n<p>Below that are poetic verses and a message with historical and spiritual themes. The letter expresses:<br \/>\nlove for the homeland.<br \/>\nAt the bottom, the authors are indicated:<br \/>\nRepublic of Kazakhstan, &#171;Kazkaita\u017eangyrtu&#187; Scientific-Restoration Institute<br \/>\nSigned by: A.M.Mukhamedzhan, N.E.Smagul.It is addressed to Shota-Aman Ydyrysuly, as a congratulatory letter from the &#171;KAZGOR&#187; Project Academy, with the signature of Professor A.Sh.Tatygulov. 2012.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"featured_media":0,"menu_order":0,"template":"","meta":{"site-sidebar-layout":"default","site-content-layout":"","ast-site-content-layout":"default","site-content-style":"default","site-sidebar-style":"default","ast-global-header-display":"","ast-banner-title-visibility":"","ast-main-header-display":"","ast-hfb-above-header-display":"","ast-hfb-below-header-display":"","ast-hfb-mobile-header-display":"","site-post-title":"","ast-breadcrumbs-content":"","ast-featured-img":"","footer-sml-layout":"","ast-disable-related-posts":"","theme-transparent-header-meta":"","adv-header-id-meta":"","stick-header-meta":"","head